The paper proposes a neural network architecture for two tasks related to speech processing: keyword spotting and voice activity detection. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Speech and Signal Processing (cs.SD), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Among these, cs.SD is the most likely category, as the paper deals with speech processing tasks. However, the paper also involves machine learning techniques and neural networks, which are relevant to cs.CL, cs.LG, and cs.AI. Finally, the paper's focus on developing novel inference algorithms suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.SY.
